cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the implementation of a blockchain-based transactive energy system, which involves privacy-preserving financial transactions and microgrid control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the system involves distributed software platforms. The paper also discusses microgrid control, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control), and software architecture, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the need for privacy-preserving financial markets, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
